id: pm-5758
title: deriveExtensionCapabilities omits 'schema' for a CommandDefinition with inline flags (manifest under-grant would fail activation)
description: "Surfaced while building describeExtensionBlueprint (pm-tlpv): `deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint)` only scanned the top-level blueprint fields, so a blueprint whose only schema-requiring surface is a command-definition's INLINE `flags` array (e.g. `commands: [{ name, run, flags: [...] }]` with no separate top-level `flags` record) derived `[\"commands\"]` and omitted `\"schema\"`.\n\nImpact: at activation `registerCommand` calls `assertExtensionCapability(extension, \"schema\", \"registerCommand flags\")` (loader.ts:1854-1855) for any command with `flags !== undefined`. An author who set `manifest.capabilities = deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint)` would therefore ship an UNDER-granted manifest that throws `extension_capability_missing` on load — the exact opposite of the helper's purpose.\n\nFix: deriveExtensionCapabilities now adds `\"schema\"` when any `blueprint.commands[].flags !== undefined`, mirroring the loader's exact guard (including an empty inline array). describeExtensionBlueprint's `flag_commands` already unions inline-flag command paths with the top-level `flags` keys, so the static summary and the capability set agree, and the describe parity test (static == runtime describeExtensionActivation) over an inline-flags blueprint pins it. Regression source: pm-iqq0 (composeExtension/deriveExtensionCapabilities). Discovered by: pm-tlpv. Was previously untested."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-22T22:00:08.557Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-22T22:02:12.649Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: deriveExtensionCapabilities now adds schema for inline-flags command definitions.
expected_result: deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint) yields a manifest grant that activates without extension_capability_missing.
actual_result: "Added schema when any blueprint.commands[].flags !== undefined; unit-tested and pinned by the inline-flags parity test."
